HEADWORD: Lipped
<hw>Lipped</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧pt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having a lip or lips; having a raised or rounded edge resembling
the lip; -- often used in composition; <as>as, thick<ex>-lipped</ex>,
thin<ex>-lipped</ex>, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Labiate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lippitude</ent>⟦br⟧
